<br>
It would be quite easy.<br>
<br>
1. Origionally create an account and get character to high level.<br>
<br>
2. Remember account name and password.<br>
<br>
3. Sell on EBay for X dollars.<br>
<br>
4. Recieve X dollars and email/mail the account information.<br>
<br>
5.  Wait like 2 or 3 days and go through the &quot;origional account owner&quot; deal people sometimes do.  All you need is the origional credit card number... I think.<br>
<br>
6. Take account back and resell for X dollars.<br>
<br>
That is probably what happened to you.  Plus you can't do @#%$ legally to the person because ebay doesn't recognize the selling of fake items (pixles). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uthrasy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thrasy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cachelaw.com/~bhadfield/leafpic.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/29/02 2:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrscammeralert.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: accounts scams (snayin)</span><hr size=1> I am posting only because I know Enantiomer and Aziline in real life and you cheated the crap out of them man.<br>
